cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper is about using very deep convolutional neural networks for large vocabulary continuous speech recognition (LVCSR), which is a topic that falls under the subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. However, the paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks for image processing (cs.CV) and the use of batch normalization (cs.LG) and sequence data (cs.SD) in deep learning models. Additionally, the paper's focus on improving accuracy and efficiency in LVCSR aligns with the goals of the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
